Kwaito king Arthur Mafokate has rejected an invite to attend the ANC Siyanqoba shindig with President Cyril Ramaphosa at Sandton Convention Centre on Thursday. Mafokate, a staunch ANC supporter and the party's most well-known celebrity campaigner, sneezed at the call to rub shoulders with Ramaphosa after the party's big wigs publicly humiliated him earlier this year. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD